  <thing id="rauEPOrgCl" name="Clinging Parts" description="If an embalmed swarm successfully damages a victim, the swarm&apos;s sinewy strands of intestine wrap around its target, attempting to constrict and crush. Anyone damaged by the swarm takes a further 1d6 points of damage on the following round as he dislodges the grasping, writhing tissues. This damage occurs (for a single round) even if the victim has successfully exited the swarm." compset="RaceSpec">
